16:32.555 --> 16:34.580
Lisa? Ham hock? Tri-tip?

16:34.691 --> 16:37.182
Do we have any food that
wasn't brutally slaughtered?

16:37.293 --> 16:39.386
Well, I think the veal might
have died of loneliness.

16:39.495 --> 16:41.486
Well, hang onto
your hoopskirts, folks...

16:41.598 --> 16:46.626
<i>because Anton Lubchenko is gonna be
kicking higher than a mule on payday.</i>

16:46.736 --> 16:49.603
<i>Oh, Land O'Lakes,
take that ozone layer.</i>

16:55.278 --> 16:59.305
<i>- What a glorious day to be that man's foot.
- [ Kiss ]</i>

17:04.921 --> 17:09.949
Whoa! Anna, get your radar gun, 'cause
that tamale was one tall drink of water.

17:10.059 --> 17:14.086
Wow. He should have his foot
insured by Lloyd's of London.

17:14.196 --> 17:17.098
<i>Oh, you just know what everyone
should do, don't you, Marge?</i>

17:17.200 --> 17:21.159
<i>-[ Gunshot ]
- Ladies and gentlemen,
pour a little cider on those peepers...</i>

17:21.271 --> 17:24.001
<i>'cause here comes the halftime parade.</i>

17:24.107 --> 17:27.201
[ Gasps ] I forgot my float.
Quick. Pass me down.

17:27.310 --> 17:30.677
[ Giggling ]
Stop that.

17:30.780 --> 17:32.680
Okay, Lise.

17:32.782 --> 17:36.809
- If they don't have tabbouleh,
what's your second choice?
- They'll have tabbouleh.

17:36.920 --> 17:40.822
You're the miracle boy
with the healing hands, arr, ain't ya?

17:40.924 --> 17:42.482
Nah. I don't do that anymore.

17:42.592 --> 17:46.585
So I guess I'll have to see someone else
about my crippling depression.

17:46.696 --> 17:49.324
Arr. Arr.

17:49.432 --> 17:51.423
Wow. And I thought he had it all.

17:52.869 --> 17:55.667
# I've had #

17:55.772 --> 17:58.434
- #The halftime of my life #
- [ Squeals ]

17:58.541 --> 18:01.977
#And I owe it all to S.U. ##

18:02.078 --> 18:05.047
An overdue tribute to halftime itself.

18:05.148 --> 18:08.948
And as those lumbering ships of
the gridiron sail off into our memories...

18:09.052 --> 18:10.952
the players return to the field.

18:11.054 --> 18:13.522
<i>[ Homer]
Ahh! Hang on!</i>

18:13.623 --> 18:15.818
<i>- And what's this?
- [ Vehicle Backfiring ]</i>

18:15.925 --> 18:21.227
Wait! Wait! I got a float too.
Listen up, 'cause I gotta explain a lot of it.

18:21.331 --> 18:24.095
- [ Booing ]
- Boo?

18:24.200 --> 18:26.430
- Hey, look out! He's nuts!
- Look out!

18:26.536 --> 18:30.597
<i>Out of the way, Baryshnikov!
[ Gasps ]</i>

18:30.707 --> 18:34.438
- [ Screams ]
- [ Gasps ] He hit the star player.

18:34.544 --> 18:37.513
Oh. Dad has the worst luck
when he's drinking.

18:38.614 --> 18:41.344
- Now does this hurt?
- [ Screams ]

18:41.451 --> 18:43.351
Just a simple yes or no.

18:43.453 --> 18:47.480
Oh, I only wanted to
show my school spirit.

18:47.590 --> 18:51.549
I wagered a large sum on the performance
of that scholar athlete.

18:53.896 --> 18:59.027
No, wait. I got a kid who's a miracle worker.
He'll heal him up real good.

18:59.135 --> 19:02.866
- Well, he'd better. Or else-
- Or else what?

19:02.972 --> 19:04.599
Oh, right. The ice pick.

19:07.110 --> 19:09.635
Bart, I need a miracle.

19:09.746 --> 19:12.442
<i>Sorry, Dad. I can't just magically
cure a broken leg.</i>

19:12.548 --> 19:14.880
<i>[ Clears Throat ]</i>

19:14.984 --> 19:19.284
Ahh! Please, Bart. You've gotta
use your powers. I'm beggin' ya.

19:20.923 --> 19:25.724
<i>- [ Groaning ]
- Son, I'm afraid that leg is hanging by a thread.</i>

19:25.828 --> 19:27.728
Lubchenko must return to game.

19:27.830 --> 19:30.799
[ Chuckling ] Oh, your playing days
are over, my friend.

19:30.900 --> 19:34.097
But you can always fall back
on your degree in... Communications?

19:34.203 --> 19:36.194
Oh, dear Lord.

19:36.305 --> 19:39.638
I know. Is phony major.
[ Sobbing ]

19:39.742 --> 19:43.007
Lubchenko learn nothing.
Nothing.

19:43.112 --> 19:45.444
Bart, do your thing.

19:45.548 --> 19:50.952
[ Gulp ] Okay, God. If you did give me
a power, let it work now.

19:51.054 --> 19:55.150
Not just for me,
but for my dad.

19:55.258 --> 19:58.455
Heal. Heal. Heal!

19:58.561 --> 20:01.155
Oh, Doctor! With S.U. behind
and seconds left...

20:01.264 --> 20:06.634
my supply of homespun sayings is lower
than a doodlebug in Aunt Tillie's root cellar.

20:06.736 --> 20:09.830
<i>- [ Crowd Cheering ]
- So we'll- Oh,jumpin' crawdaddies!</i>

20:09.939 --> 20:12.169
<i>Is that Lubchenko
coming back on the field?</i>

20:12.275 --> 20:14.573
Yea!

20:14.677 --> 20:18.044
<i>Bart did it. And they're
gonna try for a field goal.</i>

20:18.147 --> 20:21.048
A field goal?
Hmm, 1 9, 20, 21 -

20:21.150 --> 20:23.641
[ Gasps ]
That would win the game.

20:40.269 --> 20:44.103
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Cheering ]

20:45.608 --> 20:48.338
Ohh.

20:48.444 --> 20:51.345
- Aw.
- Ohh.

20:55.251 --> 20:57.845
Ohh.

20:57.954 --> 20:59.945
<i>- [ Whistle Blows ]
- [ Crowd Cheering ]</i>

21:01.357 --> 21:05.259
I did it! I did it!
My leg, it broke off.

21:07.029 --> 21:09.224
- Whoa.
- Yes!

21:11.467 --> 21:13.867
## [ Hums: Heavy Metal ]

21:16.472 --> 21:18.667
Poor guy.
He lost his leg.

21:18.774 --> 21:21.607
Oh, no, no. The fans will whoop it up
with that leg tonight.

21:21.711 --> 21:23.611
You know, drink beer
out of it and so on.

21:23.713 --> 21:26.375
But it'll turn up in the morning,
and I'll sew it back on.

21:26.482 --> 21:29.474
- Will that really work?
- Well, I assume so.

21:29.585 --> 21:34.045
- As long as I have Bart's healing powers.
- Why won't anybody listen to me?

21:34.157 --> 21:38.150
I don't have any special powers.
I am not a healer.

21:38.261 --> 21:40.559
Fine.
More money for me.

22:26.042 --> 22:28.010
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

